<p style="font-size:1.05em;">
  <strong>Frontier UI (FUI)</strong> is the Web Everything <strong>reference component library</strong> — a
  comprehensive, framework-free component set realizing the WE intents and blocks over the native substrate.
  Crucially, it appears here as an ordinary <strong>peer column</strong>, exactly like every other impl
  (ratified <a href="/backlog/1450-public-multi-impl-compatibility-table-fui-as-peer-column/">#1450</a> &rarr; A):
  its strength is <em>earned and visible</em> — the column green across the most rows — never status-declared.
  Impl-neutrality is statute; the protocol is the only lock.
</p>

<h3>Why the tiers fall where they do</h3>
<p class="text-slate-600">
  FUI is scored on the <strong>library coverage axis</strong> (<code>supported</code> / <code>partial</code> /
  <code>unsupported</code>). Its breadth comes from its block set: droplist / tree-select
  (<code>customizable-select</code>), notification / master-detail surfaces (<code>dialog</code>,
  <code>popover</code>), the rich-text editor (<code>contenteditable</code>, <code>highlight-api</code>),
  FACE-based form controls (<code>face</code>, <code>custom-state</code>, <code>request-submit</code>), and its
  pan-zoom / droplist positioning (<code>anchor-positioning</code>) — all <strong>supported</strong>.
</p>
<ul class="list-disc pl-5 text-slate-600">
  <li>
    <strong><span style="color:#92400e;">partial</span></strong> cells (<code>showpicker</code>,
    <code>field-sizing</code>, <code>dialog-closedby</code>, <code>cross-root-aria</code>,
    <code>details-name</code>, <code>hidden-until-found</code>, <code>editcontext</code>,
    <code>sanitizer-api</code>) are where FUI approximates the capability or relies on a polyfill rather than
    owning it end-to-end.
  </li>
</ul>
<p class="text-slate-600">
  Coverage shown is <strong>v1</strong>, derived from the block set and refined by the
  <a href="/backlog/1451-library-adapter-watch-keep-incumbent-lib-adapters-current/">library-adapter watch (#1451)</a>.
  That FUI is the greenest column is the table working as intended — it shows, rather than declares, the
  reference impl's reach.
</p>
